sqlcmd cheat sheet:

.help → list commands

.mode raw → show raw output

.output filename → save query results

\dt → list tables

\i file.sql → run SQL script

SELECT * FROM table; → view data

EXEC sp_columns 'dbo.table' → inspect columns

EXEC sp_help 'dbo.table' → show schema

run via: sqlcmd -S localhost:3307 -d dbname